    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-11T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="314"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d314">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4089: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan (<persName corresp="#p_FWC1" type="to"
                        >Forbes</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-11T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 11, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. Your 51, February 7, 10 p.m.; 59, February 10, 9 p.m.<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d314fn15">No. 59 not printed.</note> (last paragraph) and
                    Department’s 50, February 10, 8 p.m.<note n="16" xml:id="d314fn16">For
                        Department’s telegram No. 50, see <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_191">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 191</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Considering the serious embarrassment, not only to ourselves but to other
                    governments and agencies vitally interested in the Shanghai situation, which has
                    resulted from the miscarriage of these recent proposals, I would suggest great
                    caution on the part of your staff in relation to any such projects.</p>
                <p>I especially desire that, in case at any time another such project or a movement
                    toward formulation of such should develop, I be promptly and fully informed not
                    only regarding the project itself but regarding the source and circumstances of
                    its origin and development.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
